Central Organization of Trade Unions (COTU) boss has asked National Super Alliance (NASA) leader Raila Odinga to get ready for the repeat presidential election on October 26 and stop issuing threats that there will be no poll.
 Francis Atwoli, pointed out that Raila should stop living in denial that he was not consulted on the date announced by the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC), to conduct the fresh process. 
 ALSO READ:

Raila’s Supreme Court victory opens Pandora’s Box, lawyers say

 The COTU Secretary General further urged the former Prime Minister to campaign across the country before the showdown between him and President Uhuru Kenyatta.
 “Raila should be ready for the elections any day, he should stop living in denial that he was not consulted on the date for the repeat election. He should equip himself by campaigning across the country,” reiterated Atwoli.
